Project context:
- This repo contains a small Python data-processing script and CSV data.
- Prefer minimal, beginner-friendly code and explanations.

Coding rules:
- Use Python 3 syntax with clear variable names.
- Keep functions small and single-purpose.
- Add short docstrings for non-trivial functions.
- Handle common file/data errors with clear messages.
- Avoid adding dependencies unless explicitly requested.

Data/file handling:
- Preserve CSV schema and row order unless asked to transform it.
- Never fabricate data values; only derive from existing inputs.
- Use UTF-8 text handling for file I/O.

Editing behavior:
- Make targeted changes; do not refactor unrelated code.
- Keep comments concise and useful (no obvious comments).
- When changing behavior, include a quick way to verify (example command or expected output).
